Let $P = (x,y,z).$  Then
\begin{align*}
d_1 &= \frac{|x - z|}{\sqrt{1^2 + 0^2 + (-1)^2}} = \frac{|x - z|}{\sqrt{2}}, \\
d_2 &= \frac{|x - 2y + z|}{\sqrt{1^2 + (-2)^2 + 1^2}} = \frac{|x - 2y + z|}{\sqrt{6}}, \\
d_3 &= \frac{|x + y + z|}{\sqrt{1^2 + 1^2 + 1^2}} = \frac{|x + y + z|}{\sqrt{3}}.
\end{align*}Hence,
\[\frac{(x - z)^2}{2} + \frac{(x - 2y + z)^2}{6} + \frac{(x + y + z)^2}{3} = 36.\]This simplifies to $x^2 + y^2 + z^2 + xy - xz + yz = 36.$  Completing the square, we get
\[\left( x + \frac{y}{2} - \frac{z}{2} \right)^2 + \frac{3}{4} y^2 + \frac{3}{4} z^2 = 36.\]Then
\[\frac{\left( x + \frac{y}{2} - \frac{z}{2} \right)^2}{36} + \frac{y^2}{48} + \frac{z^2}{48} = 1.\]This is the equation of an ellipsoid centered at $\left( -\frac{y}{2} + \frac{z}{2}, 0, 0 \right),$ with semi-axes of length $6,$ $4 \sqrt{3},$ and $4 \sqrt{3}.$

